Definition: skill acquired through experience in a trade
Example: often used to discuss skill in espionage; instructional designers are trained in something that might be called tradecraft; the CIA chief of station accepted responsibility for his agents' failures of tradecraft
Synonyms: craft, skill, acquired, through, experience, in, a, trade, often, used, to, discuss, espionage, instructional, designers, are, trained, something, that, might, be, called, the, CIA, chief, of, station, accepted, responsibility, for, his, agents, failures
Category: noun.cognition
